deck: Taison, Fujio and Youkou's crazy and powerful father. He is a monk but can still beat them effortlessly.
description:
First appearing in the prototype one-shot, Bachi-Atari Rock, that would become Rokudenashi Blues; Taison's father was one of the few elements from this one-shot that fully carried over into the serial but interestingly, was a plot-twist that came up years after the start of the series.

The main difference in the premise is that in the one-shot, Taison is an only child so his father forces him to become a monk whereas in the serial, Taison is the second of three sons. His father has the same drive for his son to be a monk but since there are three of them, Taison and his older brother Fujio both ran away from home to live together far away from their father while Youkou, the youngest brother, was forced into being a monk.
name: Maeda Bunson

deck: A fictional "Golden Age Superman" archetype brought to life.
description:
Created by Ben Conrad, the Champion of the oppressed was the main character of an unfinished book whom the subcounscious mind of his writer materialized in a being pretty much similar to Superman but with methods far more directs and violents. Many of his actions ressembled the original exploits of the Golden age Superman.

Superman could stop the Champion when he confronted Conrad about their feelings about the loss sense of justice from the now sour writer and how new methods had to be reached to solve conflicts. Even if some the actions of the Champion were wronged, his motivation and ideal were in the right place.

His demise however would lead to the birth of the Hollow men.

name: Champion of the Oppressed

deck: A writer with the power of make his books reality.
description:
A veteran writer, Benjamin Conrad was a journalist whom inspired Clark Kent to consider a career as writer. In his older years, he manifested the power to materialize his books. First, it was an unpublished book called the Champion of the oppressed, whne the main character of the book became a real entity. His power would manifest again when another less know but already published book called the Hollow men manifested in the reality. With the help of Superman, Conrad averted both crisis.

He retired to Heroville.

deck: The local doctor of Heroville, and its creator.
description: Dr Camel is an expert in medicine, physics and phychology and it was the mind behind the project Heroville. Hidding the town inside a tesseract, Dr Camel destroyed all the information about the project and escape inside the dimension. When Superman discovered Heroville, Dr Camel asked him to keep the secret of his home, to avoid the culture shock and danger than the external world means to his home. Dr Camel hoever would had to face the menace of the Hollow men capable of trace the colorful location.

issue_credits.name: The Living Double of a Single Fiction

name: Dr. Camel

deck: A young citizen from Heroville.
description:
Kid Scout was an inhabitan of Heroville, the secret project to produce metahumans for the US army in the 50s. His life was the as the other kids from his community until the attack of the Hollow men. After hidding in his secret lair, Kid Scout was rescued by Superman just in time for the attack of the Hollow men. To stop the Hollow Men, Superman and his allies neede the help of the Hollow Men creator, writer Ben Conrad. With his abilities to track and transport, Kid Scout found Conrad and moved him to Heroville in time to stop the rampage of his subconscious creations.

After this adventure, Kid Scout returned to his life in the secret community.
